    "description": "Shinko Shoji Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the import, export, and sale of electronic components in Japan, rest of Asia, North America, and Europe. It operates through Electronic Device Business, Assembly Business, and Other Businesses segments. The company offers semiconductors, general electronic parts and batteries, display devices, embedded computing, and solution services, as well as integrated circuits, assembly products, and other electronic equipment. It also provides in-vehicle semiconductors and passive components, including MCU, SoC, analog, power discrete, and connectors; integrated cockpit, EV, brushless DC motor control, and data logger solutions; sensing, vision, AI, and connectivity products; gaming and casino equipment; ICT on-site solutions; edge computer controllers; design and development tools; communications and networks; and non-contact services. In addition, the company offers scheme and support systems; non-Japanese printed circuit boards and harnesses; express prototyping and procurement support services; lithium-ion and battery solutions; power generation; support services for overseas transfers and electronics manufacturing services; and design and development solutions, such as CAN+A/D data loggers, model-based development, embedded software, ASIC/FPGA, and AUTOSAR. Further, it provides workstations, supercomputers, and peripheral equipment; and engages in the contract development of microcomputer software and software development activities. The company serves the automotive, industry, amusement, AI/DX, EMS/ODM, energy, design development, logistics, and office automation markets. Shinko Shoji Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1953 and is headquartered in Shinagawa, Japan."
